title: Nucleic acid sequence - Wikipedia
snippet:
A nucleic acid sequence is a succession of base-pairs signified by a series of a 
set of five different letters that indicate the order of nucleotides forming alleles 
within a DNA (using GACT) or RNA (GACU) molecule. By convention, sequences 
are usually presented from the 5' end to the 3' end. For DNA, the sense strand is 
used.
